You might think that taking probiotics is only necessary when you are on a course of antibiotics, right? Wrong! Health starts in the gut. If your gut health is low, it can lead to digestive problems, a weakened immune system, skin problems and even mental health issues, which is why you need probiotics – always. Probiotics are beneficial micro-organisms that live in your gut and are crucial for the health of your digestive system…and your brain. This is because the gut and the brain are connected by a complex communication system that can affect your physical and mental health.  Releaf Pharmaceuticals share seven quick facts about what probiotics can do for your body: 